============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

Theorem/Law:  Euler's Identity
Branch:       Complex Analysis
Formula:      e^(iπ) + 1 = 0
Applications: Signal processing, quantum mechanics
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1748)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

