Name:          Socrates
Lived:         470 - -399
Nationality:   Greek
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Socratic method
Contribution:  Father of Western philosophy; sentenced to death; documented by Plato
Quote:         "The only true wisdom is knowing you know nothing."

Name:          Cleopatra VII
Lived:         69 - -30
Nationality:   Egyptian
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Last pharaoh of Egypt
Contribution:  Spoke 9 languages; allied with Caesar and Mark Antony; end of pharaonic era
Quote:         "I will not be triumphed over."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

